The non-bonded pair calculation algorithm tolerates a few missing pair interactions close to the cut-off. This can lead to a systematic overestimation of the pressure due to missing LJ interactions. The error in the average pressure due to missing LJ interactions is at most 0.30 bar.
The pressure error can be controlled by setting the environment variable GMX_VERLET_BUFFER_PRESSURE_TOLERANCE to the allowed error in units of bar.

